reviewText: Faced with all kinds of problems from infidelity to broken nails Valerie's (Geena Davis) troubles have just began as aliens invade her pool. She must help them acclimate to our way of life. Soon the aliens learn that earth girls are easy.They say that truth is stranger than fiction.  This movie is awfully strange so it must be true. The "out of the area" visitors are easy to keep track of when they are color-coded.  The songs were great and relevant.All of the main actors went on to bigger and I guess you can say better movies.  Another early Jim Carrey movie is "Once Bitten" (1985). The best Julie Brown movie is "Out There" (1995), where she describes certain alien appendages as being curved like the space-time continuum.This is one of those movies that you may want to put on again in the background. And look up in time for your favorite parts.Out There Starring: Bill Campbell, Wendy Schaal

reviewText: It all makes sense now!  I always wondered why Jim Carrey seemed completely out of his mind.  I would have figured it out long ago, if I'd only known from the start that he is an alien.And this film will make sense to you as well, as long as you remember that it seems to be a mashup of "Grease," "The Rocky Horror Picture Show," and maybe "Plan 9 From Outer Space."  And I'm sure that "Earth Girls are Easy" would make plenty of sense to Ed Wood as well, based upon the fact that he made so many sci-fi films that were completely nonsensical.But a film doesn't always have to make perfect sense to be entertaining or funny, and this one is surely both of those.  I'm surprised that I've never seen this film until today (2013Aug24), almost a quarter century after it released.  But it was surely worth the wait, and in reality, it might have been better to wait this long to see this film.  Maybe the fact that it has become slightly dated actually makes it even funnier?Jim Carrey is surely funny, and while watching, I thought that it might have been his first film.  After peeking around the Web, I realized this was far from it, as he had done quite a few films before this one.  But the guy that I thought perhaps stole the show:  Michael McKean, playing the "Fast Times at Ridgemont High" surfer dude ala Sean Penn, although Mr. McKean is surely older.  I even think that Mr. McKean was maybe even funnier than Mr. Penn in that iconic role.What's the theme of the film?  Well, sometimes things that are obvious are staring you right in the face:  "Earth girls are easy."  Oh, but I forgot to add, "But only if they find Mr. Right."  And while I thought that Geena Davis was very good here, all of the guys in this film were alright by me.
summary: . . . and it's really easy to like this film

reviewText: In spite of this film being slightly annoying (partly for Geena Davis's character, partly for the tacked-on music), it has redeeming values that make it worth at least a watch, and a trip back into 80's Space.The best parts are the hilarious Julie Brown songs, 'I Like 'Em Big and Stupid', and 'Cuz I'm a Blonde'.  If the rest of the movie gets on your last nerve, just skip to the Julie Brown songs, and it will be worth the price you paid!  It's too bad much of the editing that took place for the movie took out Julie stuff, which is why you should get the DVD, to have access to the deleted scenes.Other highlights are a delicious and silent Jeff Goldblum, and Jim Carrey and Damon Wayans, when you knew them when.  Also check out the always-appealing Michael McKean as a pool-cleaning Surf Bum.Combine all that with lots of 80's color and glam, and you've got a fun little trip on their alien ship.

reviewText: Ok, Geena Davis, Jeff Goldblum and practically an all star cast make this movie...  Not film, movie.  This is a fun, feel good, movie.  Aliens meet Valley Girls (gag me with a spoon) and run amok in this 1980s classic comedy.  Well, comedy just doesn't cut it!  Geena Davis, Jeff Goldblum, Jim Carrey, Damon Wayans, Julie Brown (who also co-wrote it) are ALL in it.  Why, we don't know.  But the worst to come is you'll suffer 80's flashbacks for a while.  The basics are three (80's colored) furry aliens stumble to Earth when two of them are horsing around.  Much needed repairs must happen before they can leave and much needed shore leave, or so to speak, must give them... uh, a much needed, release?  Must have been the 80's where these guys come from too.  Julie is the salon matron and maven of blonde who is recruited to make the aliens a little less, uh, well, alien.  She Nair's 'em silly and stiles their hair so any 80's dude would have serious issues with envy and finds these guys are killer!  The kick is Julie's 80s smash (or crash?) hit, "'Cause I'm A Blonde" is headlined too. in the film  Fun, fun, fun flick!

It's almost like a series of video CD's  clipped together - well, that's Temple's background, he's done the Rolling  Stones and like, and here he is making a movie! Monty Python it's not, but  it's a laugh, sometimes a good laugh!

reviewText: It's hard to say if I'd like this movie if I didn't remember the 80s. reviewText: "Earth Girls Are Easy" is a musical sci-fi comedy about valley-girl Valerie (played by Geena Davis) living in 1980's Los Angeles, and who is engaged to a cheating, boyfriend doctor named Ted (played by Charles Rocket).  Catching her boyfriend at home playing with a nurse, the disgruntled Valerie gets the surprise of her life when a spaceship crash lands in her swimming pool.  The spaceship's crew (played by Jeff Goldblum, Jim Carrey and Damon Wayans), haven't had any "shore leave" in a long time.  Not wanting to cause too much of a stir, Valerie takes the alien trio to her best friend Candy (played by Julie Brown) who owns a beauty salon.  After Candy transforms the furry trio into believable human males, Valerie finds their captain, Mac (Jeff Goldblum), very attractive.  Wild things happen when the alien trio are taken to a dance club and letting them drive in California traffic!The fact that this film is also a musical only adds to the humor as there are several original songs by Julie Brown!If you enjoy remembering the excesses of the 1980's and New Wave music, you will probably enjoy this film!

reviewText: (I noticed that there are several people on Amazon who don't know the difference between a movie review and leaving feedback.  Weird!)The film was a Netflix download and though the quality was crazy, it was fun to watch a silly musical comedy.  Directed by Julien Temple, starring Jeff Goldblum and Geena Davis who really have their comedy routines down.  An early appearance by Jim Carrey was fun to see as well.Three furry aliens have spaceship trouble and land of all places in the "like, you know" the Valley, in a swimming pool of a girl who has just broken up with her cheating doctor boyfriend.  Though the whole romance angle goes out the window, the furry aliens try to help her out.They get a shave, they party, and they charm the party girls with their very long tongues and fancy dance moves.Such songs as 'Cause I'm A Blonde", some B-52 hits and The Love Train pepper the film.  Hollywood excesses, crazy songs and crazy dialogue make this film a cult favorite.Recommended!
summary: Early Jim Carrey Makes For A Fun Film!

reviewText: If you like 'em that way too, then this is the movie for you!Four very strong leads - Geena Davis, Jeff Goldblum and then unknown Jim Carrey and Damon Williams - backed up by Julie Brown deliver a paper-thin story with humor, bright colors and an ineffable sexiness.  I think this was an attempt to revive musical-comedy cinema in the late '80s; the previous shining example being "Xanadu".  The songs are original, funny and have enjoyed cult status ever since.This is one of the first movies to show that inter-planetary romances don't have to end with an ova-depositor rammed down your throat.I recommend this movie to anyone who enjoys turing their minds off for an hour and a half of fun.

reviewText: As I sat down to be exposed to Earth Girls are Easy for the first time, I prepared myself for some of the most painful cinematography known to man. Little did I know, I was about to be exposed to one of the most delightfully entertaining and funny movies I have ever seen.Geena Davis, Jim Carey, Jeff Goldblum and Damon Wayans took a script destined for disaster and somehow created a masterpiece in its own right. The aliens, the musicals, the outlandish props and stupid plot all combined to create one amazingly entertaining movie. It is amazing to see the actors that  I mentioned when they were much younger and barely known in the industry, and to see them take such a weird movie to such a high level really displays their raw talent and shows why they eventually make it so big in the industry.I would highly recommend this movie to anyone wanting to see or show something different, bizarre and totally fun. It certainly is not an ordinary or normal movie, but then again, it was the 80s.
